ault<br />obviously being the normal "kill that particular thread" if at all<br />possible.<br /><br />Machine-killing is appropriate in some secure situations, but most of<br />the time it just makes it too damn hard to debug since the error often<br />doesn't get logged. In some situations we obviously can't avoid it,<br />but..<br /><br />               Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
